question: What is supersonic speed?
option1: When the speed of any object exceeds the speed of sound
option2: When the speed of any object exceeds the speed of light
option3: When the speed of any object exceeds 10000 m/s
answer: When the speed of any object exceeds the speed of sound
explanation: When the speed of any object exceeds the speed of sound it is said to be travelling at supersonic speed. Bullets, jet aircrafts etc. often travel at supersonic speeds.
